 HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 2107<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(9/17/02 2:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=134.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Ways of getting closer to Interstellar Travel.</span><hr size=1> If we used a Super Orion and barrelled it at the Sun to get a gravity assist, I wonder how much velocity we might gain. <br>
<br>
Also, the sunlight at closest proximity would be very intense. Suppose we used a large sail to focus this light to a small point. Intensifying it yet further. Then dropped reaction mass into it as we passed the Sun. That should be a fusion like reaction. <br>
<br>
Perhaps it might even be possible to initiate a solar flare. If the ship could withstand the plasma then additional velocity might be gained from that. Those flares can reach 10% lightspeed.<br>
<br>
We still have an almost full cargo hold of pulse units.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uzaphod4468.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zaphod4468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 1038<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(9/17/02 9:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=134.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.bbc.co.uk/cult/hitchhikers/gallery/images/100/zaphod2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/fry1.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Ways of getting closer to Interstellar Travel.</span><hr size=1> The old Star Trek slingshot idea, eh... careful... you might time-travel!<br>
<br>
